obj-740.text: With automatic lines, you control the number and position of midpoints but the direction of each segment is automatically inferred. To add a midpoint, right-click anywhere on the line.

obj-319.text: Monodraw supports advanced blending of line characters (produced by rect borders and lines). The behaviour can be controlled on a per-shape basis.

obj-664.text: With manual lines, you are in full control of the number of midpoints and the direction of each segment. To set a direction of segment, right-click on it.

obj-55.text:
- The tools in the toolbar can be activated using a single key. Hover over them to find out what it is.

- Most of the app can be driven with keyboard shortcuts. Hover over a particular element to find out whether a keyboard shortcut exists.

- Double-click on any shape to start editing it.

- To select multiple shapes, use Shift. To select the deepest shape under the mouse cursor, use Command. Double-click on a selected group to select any contained shapes.

- You can rename items in the sidebar by double-clicking them.

- Locked and hidden shapes can only be selected via the sidebar.

obj-1048.text:
Monodraw features a very powerful, highly customisable text engine. You can adjust all properties of the way text is laid out.

If you want to add text to a rect, enable “Text” from the inspector.

obj-812.text: Line labels are just text boxes attached to the line. You can add attachment points by right-clicking on the line. Labels can be added by double-clicking on the line. The position of the label is adjusted via its "Anchor Position" inspector pane.

obj-37.text: Every shape can be raw-edited. You can do so using the pencil, bucket fill or by double-clicking it. When you try to edit a rect which contains text, you will be shown a popover to edit the text content first. If you want to raw edit it, click on the “Raw Edit” button.

obj-167.text: You can add custom attachment points to rects and other shapes. To do so, right-click and select “Add Attachment Point”. If you have a bordered rect (even transparent border), you can drag the attachment point just outside the border for convenient attachment with lines.
